          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What do I need for my first meeting?",
            "answer": "<p>Bring your most recent tax returns (personal and business), current financial statements, and any questions you have. If you use accounting software, we'll ask for temporary access so we can review your books during the meeting.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq-2": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How do you charge for services?",
            "answer": "<p>Most engagements are structured as a fixed monthly fee covering bookkeeping, advisory, and tax planning. Tax preparation is quoted separately based on complexity. We provide a detailed proposal before any work begins.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq-3": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do you work with my accounting software?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. We work with QuickBooks Online, Xero, FreshBooks, Wave, and most major platforms. If you're not on one yet, we'll recommend the best fit for your business size and industry.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq-4": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "When should I start tax planning?",
            "answer": "<p>The best time is at the start of your fiscal year. The second best time is now. Tax planning is most effective when we have months — not weeks — to implement strategies. Contact us anytime to get started.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
